### Describe the bug

The fix in #17906 resulted in a regression where `const value = cache.value ??= await get_value()` no longer compiles successfully.

### Reproduction

5.53.10 can compile even if behavior is buggy: https://svelte.dev/playground/hello-world?version=5.53.10#H4sIAAAAAAAACm2Q0WqEMBBFfyUMfXBZWVvpk6su_Y5aSjYdbWg6CWbc7RLy70WtlQXfMucM94YJQPIboQBIodUGPRSvAfjmRjYCSJeNF-cO_oKGR3aWHre4ssRI7KGA0qteO64batggC2UH4idRiQfPkjF53B3vVL6tpPrE1YQ4KWpY-hsp0Q6kWFsSnU12Ioyi4blpvz8uI3kWF2mGMWgKPMzT6VQJeZWaRYf8PrFkro7bJevWXVf-39UjDz2J53xJKbP1DFSeB2ZLwpIyWn1VobOx7myZzbxuqHT1_PtChPkR07_zLCSPZeZqSIHxh6HgfsD4lgJLba6aPqBopfEYfwE5h7_C2gEAAA

5.53.11 can't compile: https://svelte.dev/playground/hello-world?version=5.53.11#H4sIAAAAAAAACm2Q0WqEMBBFfyUMfXBZWVvpk6su_Y5aSjYdbWg6CWbc7RLy70WtlQXfMucM94YJQPIboQBIodUGPRSvAfjmRjYCSJeNF-cO_oKGR3aWHre4ssRI7KGA0qteO64batggC2UH4idRiQfPkjF53B3vVL6tpPrE1YQ4KWpY-hsp0Q6kWFsSnU12Ioyi4blpvz8uI3kWF2mGMWgKPMzT6VQJeZWaRYf8PrFkro7bJevWXVf-39UjDz2J53xJKbP1DFSeB2ZLwpIyWn1VobOx7myZzbxuqHT1_PtChPkR07_zLCSPZeZqSIHxh6HgfsD4lgJLba6aPqBopfEYfwE5h7_C2gEAAA

```svelte
<script>
	let count1 = $state(0);
	let count2 = $state(0);
	let cache = $state({});

	async function go() {
		count1++;
		const value = cache.value ??= await get_value();
	}

	async function get_value() {
		count2++;
		return 42;
	}
</script>

<button onclick={go}>go</button>
<p>count1: {count1}, count2: {count2}</p>
```

This example is based on https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/pull/17906/changes#diff-cf5ed02a8526fdefc216873f8ec56f55e78dc8454605b8318d3d43fdee2dc288

### Logs

```
Error compiling component
virtual://$/App.svelte (8:21): await isn't allowed in non-async function (Note that you need plugins to import files that are not JavaScript)
```

### System Info

```shell
Svelte REPL 5.53.11
```

### Severity

annoyance

